Tragedy hits as Nigerian rapper, Biglo has been pronounced dead after a long battle with Kidney ailment. <img src="https://notjustok.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/0404B75B-B0E0-4DBE-A7BA-28FD13583C0A-420x420.jpeg"/> The announcement was made by his friend and industry colleague, Jazzman Olofin, on the 27th of December 2020, where he announced the Biglo's death, stating that he had fought bravely. Making the announcement on Instagram, Jazzman said; Dear BIGLO , heard the sad news last night you passed away. You fought bravely all the way but GOD Almighty knows best. We'll keep the fire burning. Rest in peace, bro. <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/12.0.0-1/72x72/1f64f-1f3fe.png" alt="🙏🏾"/><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/12.0.0-1/72x72/1f64f-1f3fe.png" alt="🙏🏾"/> FYI, BIGLO was a Nigerian music producer, rapper and singer. <img src="https://notjustok.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/87C31D85-8A4B-4F36-BF7F-30DC76082AD4-420x420.jpeg"/> In July 2019, there had been reports of the rapper's battle with his Kidney and also reports that he was receiving treatments in California and also asking for fans' support as the cost for dialysis is a lot. The post Veteran Rapper, Biglo Dies After Battle With Kidney Ailment appeared first on Most Trusted Voice in Music & Afrobeats from Nigeria & Africa | Notjustok. Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.